<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.35a.54.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">54</fw>
<note type="curatorial"></note>

<opener>
<dateline>May 3, 1971
</dateline>
<address>
<addrLine>Dr. John G. Neihardt</addrLine>
<addrLine>c/o Mr. Dick Cavett</addrLine>
<addrLine>ABC, New York</addrLine>
</address>
<salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
</opener>

<p>We enjoyed your show last week very much with Mr. Cavett. My Mother was born at Ft. Robinson and knew of Crazy Horse and Gen. Custer.</p>
<p>You spoke of belonging to the Omaha of Indian Wars. Perhaps you knew my grandfather, Col. Charles
Taylor, of the 9<hi rend="underline">th</hi> Cavalry. Red Cloud surrendered to him and he was a friend of Bill Cody's and Calamity Jane's.</p>
<p>My husband and I send money whenever we can to the Red Cloud Indian School in Pine Ridge, South Dakota as a token for the great wrong done to the American Indians. Their language and their religion is indeed noble and I hope can be <unclear>perserved</unclear>.</p>
<p>If you have time, I would love to hear from you, and especially if you remember my grandfather, Col. Taylor.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Cordially,</salute>
<signed>(Mrs.) Jean E. Bann<gap reason="cut off"/>
(Banning)</signed>
<note>7 Tamalpais Ave,
Belvedere, Calif. 94<gap reason="cut off"/>
94920</note>
</closer>

</div1>
